#: ../../changelog.rst:511
msgid ""
"Update the support for non-xterm terminal emulators to be opened within a "
"particular directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:514
msgid "Update URL syntax handling in :ref:`Lumina Open`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:516
msgid ""
"Update support for sticky windows to appear in the task manager on all "
"workspaces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:519
msgid ""
"Clean up a number of possible bugs with regards to how external application "
"might be launched or used. This fixes the random race condition where a "
"process finished but the thread in Lumina which called it still thinks it is"
" running."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:524
msgid ""
"Ensure that all calendar widgets on the desktop or panel update as necessary"
" to ensure the correct date is shown during multiple-day sessions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:528
msgid ""
"Add a small CLI flag to :ref:`Lumina Open` for testing the crash handler "
"(\"-testcrash\")."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:531
msgid ""
"Ensure that on FreeBSD, the disk I/O information uses instantaneous values "
"instead of system averages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:538
msgid "Lumina 0.8.6"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:540
msgid ""
"Add the ability to set system-locale overrides, used on login. This allows "
"the user to mix locale settings for the various outputs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:543
msgid ""
"Add the ability to switch the locale of the current session on the fly, "
"changing all locale settings for the current session only. These settings "
"will be used when launching any applications within that session."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:548
msgid ""
"Fix up the translation mechanisms so that everything is instantly re-"
"translated to the new locale."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:551
msgid ""
"More languages are now fully translated. Install the x11/lumina-i18n port or"
" pkg to install the localizations and enable these new localization "
"features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:555
msgid ""
"Add support for the “Actions” extension to the XDG Desktop specifications. "
"This allows applications to set a number of various actions, or alternate "
"startup routines, within their XDG desktop registration file. These actions "
"are shown within Lumina as new sub-menus within the \"Applications\" menu as"
" well as in the \"User\" button. Look for the down arrow next to the "
"application's icon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:562
msgid ""
"Change the Lumina On-Screen-Display to a different widget, allowing it to be"
" shown much faster."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:565
msgid ""
"Add new *_ifexists* functionality to any session options in "
":file:`luminaDesktop.conf`. This allows the distributor to more easily setup"
" default applications, such as the web browser or mail client, through an "
"intelligent tree of options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:570
msgid ""
"Apply a work-around for new users which fixes a bug in Fluxbox where the "
"virtual desktop windows could still be changed or closed by various Fluxbox "
"keyboard shortcuts. If an existing user wants to apply this fix, replace "
"their :file:`~/.lumina/fluxbox-keys` with :file:`/usr/local/share/Lumina-DE"
"/fluxbox-keys`. Note that this will overwrite any custom keyboard shortcuts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:577
msgid ""
"Fix some bugs in the new window detection and adjustment routines with full-"
"screen apps that modify the X session settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:580
msgid ""
"Fix a couple bugs with the automatic detection and load routines for the new"
" QtQuick plugins."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:583
msgid ""
"Add in the :kbd:`Ctrl-X` keyboard shortcut for cutting items in the "
":ref:`Insight File Manager`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:586
msgid "Fix up the active reloading of icons when the icon theme changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:592
msgid "Lumina 0.8.5"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:594
msgid ""
"The user button has received a significant speed boost, and can now be used "
"for browsing files and directories within the user’s home directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:598
msgid ""
"Desktop icons have received a large number of changes in styling, amount of "
"visible text, and functionality. There is also a new feature to "
"automatically generate plugins for items in the user’s Desktop directory, "
"where each plugin may be individually moved/changed rather than trapped "
"within a container like the “desktopview” plugin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:604
msgid ""
"Added a desktop plugin for monitoring the system hardware status such as "
"memory and CPU usage, CPU temperature, and disk I/O. This functionality "
"requires operating system support and is currently only available for PC-"
"BSD®, FreeBSD, and Debian."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:609
msgid ""
"Added a desktop plugin container for running custom QtQuick/QML scripts. "
"While there is only a single sample plugin of this type available at the "
"present time, it is now possible for users to create their own custom "
"interface plugins using the QML scripting language, which is similar to "
"JavaScript or CSS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:615
msgid ""
"Lumina has been fully translated to German, Russian, and Spanish, and "
"almost-completely translated to Catalan (89%), Chinese (61%), Estonian "
"(53%), Indonesian (76%), Polish (89%), Portuguese (89%), Portuguese-"
"Brazilian (89%), Swedish (91%), and Turkish (88%)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:620
msgid ""
"The new system for desktop plugin settings requires that any desktop plugins"
" be reset back to defaults when upgrading to this version of Lumina."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:624
msgid ""
"There is a known conflict between Qt 5.4+ and Fluxbox 1.3.7 which prevents "
"the “close” button from working on unlocked desktop plugins. To work around "
"this issue, right-click on the title for the plugin and select the “close” "
"option from the menu to remove the desktop plugin. Alternatively, you may "
"also remove desktop plugins using the :ref:`Lumina Configuration` utility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:635
msgid "Lumina 0.8.4"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:637
msgid ""
"The panel has been improved to add support for mouse tracking, variable-"
"length panels that use a percentage of the screen edge length, and the "
"ability to pin the panel to a particular location on the screen edge by "
"either corner or centered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:642
msgid ""
"Rescale the panel size if the monitor used in the previous session was a "
"different screen resolution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:645
msgid ""
"For hidden panels, 1% of the panel size is visible on the screen while it is"
" hidden, rather than using a hard-coded pixel size. This is better for high-"
"resolution screens."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:649
msgid "Remove the restriction that panels be on opposite screen edges."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:651
msgid ""
":ref:`Lumina Search` now supports the ability to change \"Files or "
"Directories\" search preferences on a temporary basis. New command-line "
"flags can be used to start searches instantly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:655
msgid ""
"Search functionality has been integrated into the :ref:`Insight File "
"Manager`. The :kbd:`Ctrl-F` keyboard shortcut or the “Search” menu option "
"will start a search for a file or directory with the current directory as "
"the starting point."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:660
msgid ""
"A “Search” button has been added to the  home directory browser in the user "
"menu. This allows the user to easily start searching for a file or directory"
" within the selected directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:664
msgid ""
"The new “Favorites” system backend is much faster and more reliable than the"
" old system of symbolic links. Existing favorites should be automatically "
"converted to the new format when you log into the new version of Lumina."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:669
msgid ""
"The :command:`lumina-fileinfo` utility can be used to view basic file "
"information, such as timestamps, owner/group information, file size, and "
"read/write permissions. If the file is an XDG desktop shortcut that the user"
" has permission to modify, this utility provides the ability to make changes"
" to that shortcut by right-clicking on files in the desktop view plugin or "
"within the :ref:`Insight File Manager` and selecting the “Properties” "
"option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:677
msgid ""
"Better application recommendations for files and URLs, especially for web "
"browsers or email clients."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:680
msgid "Major cleanup of XCB library usage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:682
msgid ""
"Hardware-brightness controls now used for PC-BSD® by default, if supported "
"by the system hardware."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:685
msgid ""
"Putting the system into the suspend state is now supported for PC-BSD® and "
"Debian."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:688
msgid "New clock display formats."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:690
msgid ""
"A large number of session cleanup and session initialization improvements, "
"including resetting the user’s previous screen brightness and audio volume "
"settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:694
msgid ""
"New default keyboard shortcuts for tiling the open windows on the screen, on"
" new user configurations only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:697
msgid ""
"Better support for the URL input format when required by an application."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:700
msgid "The user’s “log out” window appears much faster when activated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:702
msgid ""
"There is a known bug in Lumina 0.8.4 regarding “unlocked” desktop plugins. "
"The close and maximize buttons for the plugin are unresponsive when using Qt"
" 5.4.1, preventing the user from easily removing or maximizing a desktop "
"plugin. As a temporary workaround, right-click the titlebar for the unlocked"
" plugin and select close or maximize from the menu."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:713
msgid "Lumina 0.8.3"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:715
msgid ""
"Add “Application Launcher” panel plugin which allows the user to pin the "
"shortcut for an application directly to a panel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:718
msgid ""
"Add :ref:`Lumina Xconfig`, a graphical front-end to :command:`xrandr`. This "
"utility can be used to easily enable or disable additional monitors and "
"screens within the current desktop session. Shortcuts to this utility are "
"available in the user button plugin and the settings menu plugin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:724
msgid "Fix the issue with transparent system tray icons on FreeBSD 11."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:726
msgid "Add support for the XDG autostart specifications."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:728
msgid "Fix a number of bugs related to detecting and using XDG mimetypes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:730
msgid ""
"Add support for the XDG autostart specifications. More work is necessary to "
"convert the current Lumina autostart specification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:733
msgid ""
"Add some additional fallback routines to account for possible errors in "
":file:`*.desktop` files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:736
msgid ""
"Add support for creating new (empty) files using :ref:`Insight File "
"Manager`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:739
msgid ""
"Add an option for enabling and disabling the use of image thumbnails. This "
"is useful if you have massive image directories, just be sure to disable "
"thumbnails **before** loading the directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:743
msgid ""
"Add initial drag-and-drop support for moving files and directories within a "
"directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:746
msgid "Load the specific icon for any application shortcuts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:748
msgid "Add the ability to view file checksums."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:750
msgid ""
"Add some additional checks and excludes for copy/move operations in the "
"background to prevent the user from performing illegal operations, such as "
"moving a directory into itself."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:754
msgid ""
"Add support for listing statistics about the current directory such as "
"number of files, total size of files, and percent of the filesystem which is"
" used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:758
msgid ""
"Streamline the frequency of the background directory checker so that it runs"
" much less often."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:761
msgid ""
"Disable the shutdown/restart options on PC-BSD® if the system is in the "
"middle of performing updates in order to add an extra layer of safety."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:765
msgid ""
"Have the shutdown/restart options use the “-o” option on FreeBSD and PC-BSD®"
" so that the system performs the action much faster."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:768
msgid ""
"Add support for thumbnails, increasing/decreasing icon sizes, removing "
"files, and  cut/copy files to the “desktopview” desktop plugin. This plugin "
"provides traditional desktop icons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:772
msgid ""
"Add support for increasing and decreasing the icon size for the application "
"launcher desktop plugin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:775
msgid ""
"Update the icon used for the “favorites” system in the user button and the "
"file manager."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:778
msgid ""
"Add the ability to display alternate timezones in the system clock. This "
"does **not** change the system time as it is just a setting for the visual "
"clocks/plugins."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:782
msgid ""
"Add a new panel plugin for pinning application shortcuts directly to the "
"panel. This is just like the “applauncher” desktop plugin, but on the panel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:786
msgid ""
"Perform the initial search for applications on the system within the session"
" initialization. This ensure that buttons and plugins are responsive as soon"
" as the desktop becomes visible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:790
msgid ""
"Fix an issue with transparent system tray icons on FreeBSD 11 and convert "
"the system tray embed/unembed routines to use the XCB library instead of "
"XLib."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:798
msgid "Lumina 0.8.2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:800
msgid ""
"Added :command:`lumina-info` which can be used to display information about "
"the Lumina desktop, such as the version, license, and link to the source "
"repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:804
msgid ""
"Large overhaul of the theme templates and color schemes which are available "
"out-of-box."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:807
msgid ""
"The :command:`lumina-config` utility has been rearranged so that its UI is "
"more intuitive and there is a new dialog for selecting plugins. It now has "
"the  ability to set preferred time and date formats and the ability to reset"
" default applications back to their default, non-mimetype registrations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:813
msgid ""
"The :ref:`Insight File Manager` has been improved. All file operations "
"happen in a separate thread so that the UI does not lag any more and the "
"detection of Qt-editable image files has been fixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:817
msgid ""
"Added support to update the vertical panel display of the clock plugin. "
"Various desktop plugin stability issues have been fixed and the  session "
"cleanup routine has been streamlined. A second panel is now supported and "
"the number of filesystem watchers has been reduced to one per-session "
"instead of one per-screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:823
msgid ""
":ref:`Lumina Search` can now be configured to exclude directories from a "
"\"Files or Directories\" search and to set an alternate start directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:831
msgid "Lumina 0.8.1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:833
msgid "New \"Audio Player\" desktop plugin to play audio files from the desktop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:836
msgid ""
"New \"Home Button\" panel plugin to hide all windows and show the desktop "
"and new \"Start Menu\" panel plugin which provides an alternative to the "
"user button for traditional system management."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:840
msgid ""
"Added the ability to remove or rotate image files while viewing a slideshow "
"with :ref:`Insight File Manager`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:843
msgid ""
"New backend distribution framework for setting system-wide defaults. This "
"affects new users only as existing settings will not be changed. Also added "
"the ability to reset the desktop back to its defaults using the :ref:`Lumina"
" Configuration` utility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:848
msgid ""
"Allow a customizable user icon which is also used in PCDM (PC-BSD® Display "
"Manager)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:851
msgid "Panels and desktop plugins follow the current theme by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:853
msgid ""
"The \"Note Pad\" desktop plugin has been converted to a file-based utility "
"so that all notes can be found in :file:`~/Notes` for access by other "
"utilities. Plugins are able to load a generic text file to treat like a note"
" for watching or updating."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:858
msgid ""
"Auto-hidden panels now stay visible when the mouse moves over the system "
"tray."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:861
msgid ""
"The user button opens faster now as it updates the widget on-demand in the "
"background."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:864
msgid ""
"Fixed a bug in :ref:`Lumina Open` for filenames containing multiple \".\"s "
"not detecting the file extension."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:867
msgid ""
"The log-out window now opens on the current screen and the log-out window is"
" hidden at the start of the log-out procedure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:874
msgid "Lumina 0.8.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:876
msgid "Converted to Qt5 with XCB."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:878
msgid ""
"New task manager mode which provides traditional task manager functionality."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:881
msgid ""
"Task manager right-click action menu has many more options that are auto-"
"generated based on the current window state."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:884
msgid "Better crash reporting through :ref:`Lumina Open`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:886
msgid "Better multimedia support using the new QMultimedia framework in Qt5."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:888
msgid ""
"New custom-written single-application framework with no external "
"dependencies so it works on all operating systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:891
msgid ""
"New windows are no longer placed underneath Lumina panels, even on multi-"
"monitor systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:894
msgid ""
"Special localized characters are now recognized when passed in from the "
"command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:897
msgid ""
"Recursive file operations now function properly in :ref:`Insight File "
"Manager`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:900
msgid ""
"XDG \"Exec\" field code replacements function better, which fixes KDE "
"application shortcuts like Okular."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:907
msgid "Lumina 0.7.2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:909
msgid "Streamlined startup process and utilities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:911
msgid "Enabled login and logout chimes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:913
msgid "Added the \"Note Pad\" and \"Desktop View\" desktop plugins."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:915
msgid "Added the :ref:`Lumina Search` utility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:917
msgid ""
"New color schemes: Green, Gold, Purple, Red, and Glass, with Glass as the "
"default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:920
msgid ""
"New backend system for registering default applications using mime-types "
"instead of extensions. While all Lumina utilities have been updated to work "
"with the new system, previously registered defaults might not be "
"transferred. You may need to reset your default web browser and email client"
" using the :ref:`Lumina Configuration` utility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:931
msgid "Lumina 0.6.2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:933
msgid ""
"A desktop plugin system has been implemented with two plugins: a calendar "
"and an application launcher plugin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:936
msgid ""
"The panel plugin system has been refined with transparency support for the "
"panel itself and automatic plugin resizing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:939
msgid ""
"Added the system dashboard panel plugin which allows control over the audio "
"volume, screen brightness, and current workspace, while also displaying the "
"current battery status, if applicable, and containing a button to let the "
"user log out or shutdown/restart the system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:944
msgid ""
"The user button panel plugin has been re-implemented, incorporating the "
"functionality of the desktopbar plugin. Now the user has quick access to "
"files and applications in the :file:`~/Desktop` folder, as well as the "
"ability to add and remove shortcuts to system applications in the desktop "
"folder with one click."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:950
msgid "New backgrounds wallpapers and a project logo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:952
msgid ""
"Add the :ref:`Insight File Manager`. Its features include the ability to "
"browse the system and bookmark favorite directories. It includes a simple "
"multimedia player for playing and previewing multimedia files, an image "
"slideshow viewer for previewing image files, full file and directory restore"
" functionality if ZFS snapshots are available, menu shortcuts to quickly "
"browse attached or mounted devices, tabbing support for browsing multiple "
"directories at once, and standard file and directory management such as "
"copy/paste/delete/create. Supported multimedia and image formats are auto-"
"detected, so if a particular file is not recognized, install the appropriate"
" library or plugin to provide support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:964
msgid ""
"Add :ref:`Lumina Screenshot`, a simple utility to create and save "
"screenshots. It can capture the entire system or individual windows. It can "
"delay the image capture for a few seconds as necessary. This utility is "
"automatically assigned to the “Print Screen” keyboard shortcut and is also "
"listed in the application registry under \"utilities\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:971
msgid ""
"Add a new implementation of the :ref:`Lumina Configuration` utility. It can "
"now be used to configure desktop appearance such as the background image and"
" to add desktop plugins, configure the location, color, transparency, and "
"size of panels as well as manage their plugins, with up to two panels "
"supported per screen, configure menu plugins, manage global keyboard "
"shortcuts, including shortcuts for adjusting audio volume or screen "
"brightness, manage default applications for the system by categories or "
"individually, manage session options such as enable numlock on log in or to "
"play audio chimes, manage applications and files to be launched on log in, "
"and to manage window system options such as appearance, mouse focus policy, "
"window placement policy, and the number of workspaces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:984
msgid ""
"Update the overall appearance of the application selector window in "
":ref:`Lumina Open`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:987
msgid ""
"Fully support registered mime-types on the system and recommend those "
"applications as appropriate."
msgstr ""
